{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e0952fe9-b858-40ad-8125-87986bb2819d","content":"No existing files found, so I'll provide the conversion pattern directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage` (or any element where the binding context is set). This tells the XAML compiler the expected type, enabling compile-time validation.\n\n**Before:**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**After (compiled bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nKey changes:\n1. Added `xmlns:vm` pointing to the ViewModel's namespace.\n2. Added `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage`.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, the XAML compiler validates property names and types. To ensure errors **fail the build**, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n    <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for invalid compiled bindings. Now a typo like `{Binding Thme}` will produce a **build error** instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n### Tips\n- You can scope `x:DataType` to any element (e.g., a `DataTemplate`) — it doesn't have to be page-level.\n- Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` to opt out of compiled bindings for a subtree (e.g., when using dynamic binding contexts).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e37cedb-f0d5-4c37-ab42-56ffb251b1ff","outputTokens":646,"requestId":"6C15:282BC0:7C1C0B:847FE2:6A0AF58B"},"id":"370d23f1-38fe-4858-ae50-0213c4f6efe3","timestamp":"2026-05-18T11:18:47.999Z","parentId":"081e648b-6f64-422b-897f-59c430c8de6f"}
